      • registerTabs

        protected void registerTabs​(Tab... tabs)
        Subclasses may choose whether to instantiate initial tabs on demand with createInitialTabs() or register them at once with this method. Supplied tabs would get a chance to build UI at a proper moment some time later (with Modifiable.init() call.

        The method may be invoked few times before the UI is created, registered tabs sum up.

        Parameters:
        tabs - initial set of tabs

      • createInitialTabs

        protected Collection<Tab> createInitialTabs()
        Provides initial set of tabs to appear in the UI. Subclasses may override or could use registerTabs(Tab...) instead. Note, tabs supplied would get initialized from EDT thread some moment later, when deemed appropriate (i.e. there's no guarantee all tabs get initialized, chances are implementation may opt to initialize visible tabs only)
